" title=\"Ghusl\">Ghusl</a></i></li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Tayammum\" title=\"Tayammum\">Tayammum</a></i></li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Miswak\" title=\"Miswak\">Miswak</a></i></li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Najis\" title=\"Najis\">Najis</a></i></li></ul>\n</div></td>\n</tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.1em\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_dietary_laws\" title=\"Islamic dietary laws\">Dietary</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"hlist\">\n<ul><li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Dhabihah\" title=\"Dhabihah\">Dhabihah</a></i></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_dietary_laws#Alcohol\" title=\"Islamic dietary laws\">Alcohol</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_dietary_laws#Pork\" title=\"Islamic dietary laws\">Pork</a></li></ul>\n</div>\n<ul><li><span class=\"nowrap\"><a href=\"/wiki/Comparison_of_Islamic_and_Jewish_dietary_laws\" title=\"Comparison of Islamic and Jewish dietary laws\">Comparison with <i>kashrut</i></a></span></li></ul></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame collapsed\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;background:lavender;padding-left:0.4em;text-align:center;padding-right:0.4em;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_military_jurisprudence\" title=\"Islamic military jurisprudence\">Military</a></div><div class=\"NavContent plainlist\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center;padding-left:1.5em;padding-right:1.5em;\">\n<ul><li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Jihad\" title=\"Jihad\">Jihad</a></i></li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Hudna\" title=\"Hudna\">Hudna</a></i></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Istijarah\" title=\"Istijarah\"><i>Istijarah</i> <span style=\"font-size:90%;\">(asylum)</span></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Prisoners_of_war_in_Islam\" title=\"Prisoners of war in Islam\">Prisoners of war</a></li></ul></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0.3em 0.4em 0.3em;font-weight:bold;border-top: 1px solid #aaa; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa;padding-top:0.1em;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_studies\" title=\"Islamic studies\">Islamic studies</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding-top: 0.6em;\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Fiqh\" title=\"Template:Fiqh\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Fiqh\" title=\"Template talk:Fiqh\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Fiqh&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>\u1e25ai\u1e93</b> (\u062d\u064a\u0636 menses) is the religious state of <a href=\"/wiki/Menstruation\" title=\"Menstruation\">menstruation</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Islam\" title=\"Islam\">Islam</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Menstruation relates to various purity related restrictions in <a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_sexual_jurisprudence\" title=\"Islamic sexual jurisprudence\">Islamic sexual jurisprudence</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Muslim women that are going through menstrual bleeding are exempt from <a href=\"/wiki/Fasting_in_Islam\" title=\"Fasting in Islam\">fasting</a> during the <a href=\"/wiki/Ramadan\" title=\"Ramadan\">Ramadan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Menstruation_in_Islam&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Ghulamali Ismail Naji  <i>Family Life in Islam</i>  1973 Page v \"The Prophet (S.A.) thereupon explained to her in clear words that the abnormal flow of blood after the scheduled period of 'Haiz' (menses) was not menstrual, detailing the fact that menstrual blood is more viscous than normal blood, during\"</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Jaffur Shurreef, Gerhard Andreas Herklots <i>Islam in India</i> 8171568068 Page 53  1921 \"The illness at the lunar periods is expressed by ' the approach of the menses ' (haiz and), v the arrival of the season for bathing ' (nihanl diid), ' the head becoming dirty ' (sir mailil hond), ' becoming unfit for prayers ' (benamdzl dnd), \"</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Majid Mohammadi <i>Political Islam in Post-revolutionary Iran</i> 1848852762 2015 Page 24 \"in the authenticity of Islamic texts and a clerical understanding of these texts is projected to be not only a religious threat ... \u0304 (the scholars of Islamic law) is not merely to teach haiz and nefa \u0304s (menstruating and puerperiums, purity of women); ...\"</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Ayatullah Sayyid Abulqasim al-Khui <i>Islamic Laws of Ayatullah Khui</i> 1312532505  2014 \"Atonement for sexual intercourse with a haiz is coined gold weighing 3.457 grams for the first part, 1.729 grams for the second part and 0.865 grams for the third part of the period of menses. For example if blood is discharged from the body of ..\"</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Frisk, Sylva (2009). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=jqqBn3pqiZkC&amp;pg=PA121\"><i>Submitting to God: Women and Islam in Urban Malaysia</i></a>. NIAS Press. p.&#160;121. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/8776940489\" title=\"Special:BookSources/8776940489\">8776940489</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">30 May</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Submitting+to+God%3A+Women+and+Islam+in+Urban+Malaysia&amp;rft.pages=121&amp;rft.pub=NIAS+Press&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.isbn=8776940489&amp;rft.aulast=Frisk&amp;rft.aufirst=Sylva&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DjqqBn3pqiZkC%26pg%3DPA121&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMenstruation+in+Islam\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Allah-green.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Allah-green.svg/29px-Allah-green.svg.png\" width=\"29\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Allah-green.svg/43px-Allah-green.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Allah-green.svg/57px-Allah-green.svg.png 2x\" d